diff:1612653018:1612327308:=63,80d62%0a%3c #foxbegin 210206-231018-680180#%0a%3c (:div1 class=messagehead:)%0a%3c >>rfloat%3c%3c   %0a%3c [-06.02.2021 - 15:10-] &nbsp; %0a%3c >>%3c%3c%0a%3c (:if1 authgroup @tas:)%0a%3c >>rfloat%3c%3c%0a%3c {[foxdelrange button 210206-231018-680180 {$FullName} ]}%0a%3c >>%3c%3c%0a%3c (:if1end:)%0a%3c !!!!!sarah_tandean%0a%3c (:div1end:) %0a%3c >>messageitem%3c%3c %0a%3c ''''''%0a%3c >>messageitem%3c%3c%0a%3c I think that if someone has an accent when speaking a certain language, it's because that language contains consonant or vowel sounds that don't exist in their native language. So probably if you tried to replicate a sound by doing the necessary tongue position etc and practice it enough, you would be able to diminish your accent. Adding on to what Emma said, I think that it's easier for children to do this because in general, the older you get, the harder it is to learn new skills. %0a%3c >>%3c%3c%0a%3c #foxend 210206-231018-680180#%0a
